{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1303,"text":"A few years ago,"},{"time":2487,"text":"with my colleague, Emmanuelle Charpentier,"},{"time":5281,"text":"I invented a new technology\nfor editing genomes."},{"time":9093,"text":"It's called CRISPR-Cas9."},{"time":11870,"text":"The CRISPR technology allows\nscientists to make changes"},{"time":15470,"text":"to the DNA in cells"},{"time":17349,"text":"that could allow us\nto cure genetic disease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21196,"text":"You might be interested to know"},{"time":22712,"text":"that the CRISPR technology came about\nthrough a basic research project"},{"time":26520,"text":"that was aimed at discovering\nhow bacteria fight viral infections."},{"time":31340,"text":"Bacteria have to deal with viruses\nin their environment,"},{"time":34236,"text":"and we can think about a viral infection\nlike a ticking time bomb --"},{"time":37924,"text":"a bacterium has only a few minutes\nto defuse the bomb"},{"time":41306,"text":"before it gets destroyed."},{"time":43284,"text":"So, many bacteria have in their cells\nan adaptive immune system called CRISPR,"},{"time":48698,"text":"that allows them to detect\nviral DNA and destroy it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":53148,"text":"Part of the CRISPR system\nis a protein called Cas9,"},{"time":57140,"text":"that's able to seek out, cut\nand eventually degrade viral DNA"},{"time":63113,"text":"in a specific way."},{"time":65054,"text":"And it was through our research"},{"time":66580,"text":"to understand the activity\nof this protein, Cas9,"},{"time":70261,"text":"that we realized that we could\nharness its function"},{"time":73116,"text":"as a genetic engineering technology --"},{"time":76546,"text":"a way for scientists to delete or insert\nspecific bits of DNA into cells"},{"time":83521,"text":"with incredible precision --"},{"time":85576,"text":"that would offer opportunities"},{"time":87267,"text":"to do things that really haven't\nbeen possible in the past."}]},{"cues":[{"time":91184,"text":"The CRISPR technology\nhas already been used"},{"time":93270,"text":"to change the DNA in the cells\nof mice and monkeys,"},{"time":98378,"text":"other organisms as well."},{"time":100527,"text":"Chinese scientists showed recently"},{"time":102306,"text":"that they could even use\nthe CRISPR technology"},{"time":104489,"text":"to change genes in human embryos."},{"time":107142,"text":"And scientists in Philadelphia showed\nthey could use CRISPR"},{"time":110309,"text":"to remove the DNA\nof an integrated HIV virus"},{"time":115176,"text":"from infected human cells."}]},{"cues":[{"time":118217,"text":"The opportunity to do this kind\nof genome editing"},{"time":121372,"text":"also raises various ethical issues\nthat we have to consider,"},{"time":124679,"text":"because this technology can be employed\nnot only in adult cells,"},{"time":128671,"text":"but also in the embryos of organisms,"},{"time":131298,"text":"including our own species."},{"time":134767,"text":"And so, together with my colleagues,"},{"time":136789,"text":"I've called for a global conversation\nabout the technology that I co-invented,"},{"time":141301,"text":"so that we can consider all of the ethical\nand societal implications"},{"time":145865,"text":"of a technology like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":148056,"text":"What I want to do now is tell you\nwhat the CRISPR technology is,"},{"time":153019,"text":"what it can do,"},{"time":154497,"text":"where we are today"},{"time":155766,"text":"and why I think we need to take\na prudent path forward"},{"time":158812,"text":"in the way that we employ this technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":163085,"text":"When viruses infect a cell,\nthey inject their DNA."},{"time":167363,"text":"And in a bacterium,"},{"time":168863,"text":"the CRISPR system allows that DNA\nto be plucked out of the virus,"},{"time":173752,"text":"and inserted in little bits\ninto the chromosome --"},{"time":177621,"text":"the DNA of the bacterium."},{"time":179937,"text":"And these integrated bits of viral DNA\nget inserted at a site called CRISPR."},{"time":186032,"text":"CRISPR stands for clustered regularly\ninterspaced short palindromic repeats."},{"time":192051,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":193076,"text":"A big mouthful -- you can see why\nwe use the acronym CRISPR."},{"time":196890,"text":"It's a mechanism that allows cells\nto record, over time,"},{"time":200902,"text":"the viruses they have been exposed to."},{"time":203608,"text":"And importantly, those bits of DNA\nare passed on to the cells' progeny,"},{"time":208315,"text":"so cells are protected from viruses\nnot only in one generation,"},{"time":212872,"text":"but over many generations of cells."},{"time":215245,"text":"This allows the cells\nto keep a record of infection,"},{"time":219554,"text":"and as my colleague,\nBlake Wiedenheft, likes to say,"},{"time":222517,"text":"the CRISPR locus is effectively\na genetic vaccination card in cells."},{"time":228572,"text":"Once those bits of DNA have been inserted\ninto the bacterial chromosome,"},{"time":233094,"text":"the cell then makes a little copy\nof a molecule called RNA,"},{"time":237317,"text":"which is orange in this picture,"},{"time":239356,"text":"that is an exact replicate\nof the viral DNA."},{"time":244502,"text":"RNA is a chemical cousin of DNA,"},{"time":246862,"text":"and it allows interaction\nwith DNA molecules"},{"time":250839,"text":"that have a matching sequence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":253258,"text":"So those little bits of RNA\nfrom the CRISPR locus"},{"time":257191,"text":"associate -- they bind --\nto protein called Cas9,"},{"time":261004,"text":"which is white in the picture,"},{"time":262963,"text":"and form a complex that functions\nlike a sentinel in the cell."},{"time":267206,"text":"It searches through all\nof the DNA in the cell,"},{"time":270644,"text":"to find sites that match\nthe sequences in the bound RNAs."},{"time":274920,"text":"And when those sites are found --"},{"time":276579,"text":"as you can see here,\nthe blue molecule is DNA --"},{"time":280073,"text":"this complex associates with that DNA"},{"time":282946,"text":"and allows the Cas9 cleaver\nto cut up the viral DNA."},{"time":288272,"text":"It makes a very precise break."},{"time":292096,"text":"So we can think of the Cas9 RNA\nsentinel complex"},{"time":296520,"text":"like a pair of scissors\nthat can cut DNA --"},{"time":299725,"text":"it makes a double-stranded break\nin the DNA helix."},{"time":302985,"text":"And importantly,\nthis complex is programmable,"},{"time":306991,"text":"so it can be programmed to recognize\nparticular DNA sequences,"},{"time":312215,"text":"and make a break in the DNA at that site."}]},{"cues":[{"time":315928,"text":"As I'm going to tell you now,"},{"time":317532,"text":"we recognized that that activity\ncould be harnessed for genome engineering,"},{"time":322332,"text":"to allow cells to make\na very precise change to the DNA"},{"time":326583,"text":"at the site where\nthis break was introduced."},{"time":329558,"text":"That's sort of analogous"},{"time":330797,"text":"to the way that we use\na word-processing program"},{"time":333529,"text":"to fix a typo in a document."}]},{"cues":[{"time":337541,"text":"The reason we envisioned using\nthe CRISPR system for genome engineering"},{"time":342383,"text":"is because cells have the ability\nto detect broken DNA"},{"time":346026,"text":"and repair it."},{"time":347780,"text":"So when a plant or an animal cell detects\na double-stranded break in its DNA,"},{"time":352735,"text":"it can fix that break,"},{"time":354356,"text":"either by pasting together\nthe ends of the broken DNA"},{"time":357907,"text":"with a little, tiny change\nin the sequence of that position,"},{"time":362041,"text":"or it can repair the break by integrating\na new piece of DNA at the site of the cut."},{"time":369054,"text":"So if we have a way to introduce\ndouble-stranded breaks into DNA"},{"time":374051,"text":"at precise places,"},{"time":375655,"text":"we can trigger cells\nto repair those breaks,"},{"time":378488,"text":"by either the disruption or incorporation\nof new genetic information."},{"time":383936,"text":"So if we were able to program\nthe CRISPR technology"},{"time":387202,"text":"to make a break in DNA"},{"time":389549,"text":"at the position at or near a mutation\ncausing cystic fibrosis, for example,"},{"time":395842,"text":"we could trigger cells\nto repair that mutation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":400464,"text":"Genome engineering is actually not new,\nit's been in development since the 1970s."},{"time":405591,"text":"We've had technologies for sequencing DNA,"},{"time":408366,"text":"for copying DNA,"},{"time":409985,"text":"and even for manipulating DNA."},{"time":412969,"text":"And these technologies\nwere very promising,"},{"time":416129,"text":"but the problem was\nthat they were either inefficient,"},{"time":420559,"text":"or they were difficult enough to use"},{"time":422916,"text":"that most scientists had not adopted them\nfor use in their own laboratories,"},{"time":427742,"text":"or certainly for many\nclinical applications."},{"time":432722,"text":"So, the opportunity to take a technology\nlike CRISPR and utilize it has appeal,"},{"time":440101,"text":"because of its relative simplicity."},{"time":443126,"text":"We can think of older\ngenome engineering technologies"},{"time":446919,"text":"as similar to having\nto rewire your computer"},{"time":450602,"text":"each time you want to run\na new piece of software,"},{"time":454396,"text":"whereas the CRISPR technology\nis like software for the genome,"},{"time":458184,"text":"we can program it easily,\nusing these little bits of RNA."}]},{"cues":[{"time":462658,"text":"So once a double-stranded\nbreak is made in DNA,"},{"time":465775,"text":"we can induce repair,"},{"time":467886,"text":"and thereby potentially achieve\nastounding things,"},{"time":471356,"text":"like being able to correct mutations\nthat cause sickle cell anemia"},{"time":475539,"text":"or cause Huntington's Disease."},{"time":477914,"text":"I actually think that the first\napplications of the CRISPR technology"},{"time":481399,"text":"are going to happen in the blood,"},{"time":483692,"text":"where it's relatively easier\nto deliver this tool into cells,"},{"time":488469,"text":"compared to solid tissues."}]},{"cues":[{"time":491905,"text":"Right now, a lot of the work\nthat's going on"},{"time":494333,"text":"applies to animal models\nof human disease, such as mice."},{"time":498326,"text":"The technology is being used to make\nvery precise changes"},{"time":501619,"text":"that allow us to study the way\nthat these changes in the cell's DNA"},{"time":506814,"text":"affect either a tissue or,\nin this case, an entire organism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":511515,"text":"Now in this example,"},{"time":512746,"text":"the CRISPR technology\nwas used to disrupt a gene"},{"time":516563,"text":"by making a tiny change in the DNA"},{"time":519354,"text":"in a gene that is responsible\nfor the black coat color of these mice."},{"time":524219,"text":"Imagine that these white mice\ndiffer from their pigmented litter-mates"},{"time":529261,"text":"by just a tiny change at one gene\nin the entire genome,"},{"time":533952,"text":"and they're otherwise completely normal."},{"time":535966,"text":"And when we sequence the DNA\nfrom these animals,"},{"time":538881,"text":"we find that the change in the DNA"},{"time":541531,"text":"has occurred at exactly the place\nwhere we induced it,"},{"time":544697,"text":"using the CRISPR technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":547662,"text":"Additional experiments\nare going on in other animals"},{"time":550410,"text":"that are useful for creating models\nfor human disease,"},{"time":554529,"text":"such as monkeys."},{"time":556156,"text":"And here we find\nthat we can use these systems"},{"time":559406,"text":"to test the application of this technology\nin particular tissues,"},{"time":563232,"text":"for example, figuring out how to deliver\nthe CRISPR tool into cells."},{"time":568329,"text":"We also want to understand better"},{"time":570501,"text":"how to control the way\nthat DNA is repaired after it's cut,"},{"time":574152,"text":"and also to figure out how to control\nand limit any kind of off-target,"},{"time":579857,"text":"or unintended effects\nof using the technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":584356,"text":"I think that we will see\nclinical application of this technology,"},{"time":590530,"text":"certainly in adults,"},{"time":592066,"text":"within the next 10 years."},{"time":593693,"text":"I think that it's likely\nthat we will see clinical trials"},{"time":596851,"text":"and possibly even approved\ntherapies within that time,"},{"time":600304,"text":"which is a very exciting thing\nto think about."},{"time":603041,"text":"And because of the excitement\naround this technology,"},{"time":605566,"text":"there's a lot of interest\nin start-up companies"},{"time":608883,"text":"that have been founded\nto commercialize the CRISPR technology,"},{"time":613669,"text":"and lots of venture capitalists"},{"time":615182,"text":"that have been investing\nin these companies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":619242,"text":"But we have to also consider"},{"time":620839,"text":"that the CRISPR technology can be used\nfor things like enhancement."},{"time":624485,"text":"Imagine that we could try\nto engineer humans"},{"time":627553,"text":"that have enhanced properties,\nsuch as stronger bones,"},{"time":632012,"text":"or less susceptibility\nto cardiovascular disease"},{"time":636107,"text":"or even to have properties"},{"time":637642,"text":"that we would consider maybe\nto be desirable,"},{"time":640065,"text":"like a different eye color\nor to be taller, things like that."},{"time":645942,"text":"\"Designer humans,\" if you will."},{"time":648780,"text":"Right now, the genetic information"},{"time":651194,"text":"to understand what types of genes\nwould give rise to these traits"},{"time":655711,"text":"is mostly not known."},{"time":657468,"text":"But it's important to know"},{"time":658738,"text":"that the CRISPR technology gives us a tool\nto make such changes,"},{"time":663047,"text":"once that knowledge becomes available."}]},{"cues":[{"time":666651,"text":"This raises a number of ethical questions\nthat we have to carefully consider,"},{"time":670786,"text":"and this is why I and my colleagues\nhave called for a global pause"},{"time":675025,"text":"in any clinical application\nof the CRISPR technology in human embryos,"},{"time":679795,"text":"to give us time"},{"time":680970,"text":"to really consider all of the various\nimplications of doing so."},{"time":685743,"text":"And actually, there is an important\nprecedent for such a pause"},{"time":689610,"text":"from the 1970s,"},{"time":690953,"text":"when scientists got together"},{"time":692841,"text":"to call for a moratorium\non the use of molecular cloning,"},{"time":696695,"text":"until the safety of that technology\ncould be tested carefully and validated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":703506,"text":"So, genome-engineered humans\nare not with us yet,"},{"time":708670,"text":"but this is no longer science fiction."},{"time":712179,"text":"Genome-engineered animals and plants\nare happening right now."},{"time":717069,"text":"And this puts in front of all of us\na huge responsibility,"},{"time":721146,"text":"to consider carefully\nboth the unintended consequences"},{"time":725747,"text":"as well as the intended impacts\nof a scientific breakthrough."}]},{"cues":[{"time":730190,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":731366,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":739572,"text":"(Applause ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":741535,"text":"Bruno Giussani: Jennifer, this is\na technology with huge consequences,"},{"time":745453,"text":"as you pointed out."},{"time":746628,"text":"Your attitude about asking for a pause\nor a moratorium or a quarantine"},{"time":751824,"text":"is incredibly responsible."},{"time":754733,"text":"There are, of course,\nthe therapeutic results of this,"},{"time":757305,"text":"but then there are the un-therapeutic ones"},{"time":759479,"text":"and they seem to be the ones\ngaining traction,"},{"time":761683,"text":"particularly in the media."},{"time":762953,"text":"This is one of the latest issues\nof The Economist -- \"Editing humanity.\""},{"time":767143,"text":"It's all about genetic enhancement,\nit's not about therapeutics."},{"time":771541,"text":"What kind of reactions\ndid you get back in March"},{"time":773847,"text":"from your colleagues in the science world,"},{"time":775888,"text":"when you asked or suggested"},{"time":777270,"text":"that we should actually pause this\nfor a moment and think about it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":781054,"text":"Jennifer Doudna: My colleagues\nwere actually, I think, delighted"},{"time":784079,"text":"to have the opportunity\nto discuss this openly."},{"time":786348,"text":"It's interesting that as I talk to people,"},{"time":788718,"text":"my scientific colleagues\nas well as others,"},{"time":791210,"text":"there's a wide variety\nof viewpoints about this."},{"time":793544,"text":"So clearly it's a topic that needs\ncareful consideration and discussion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":797242,"text":"BG: There's a big meeting\nhappening in December"},{"time":799481,"text":"that you and your colleagues are calling,"},{"time":801481,"text":"together with the National Academy\nof Sciences and others,"},{"time":804272,"text":"what do you hope will come\nout of the meeting, practically?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":807588,"text":"JD: Well, I hope that we can air the views"},{"time":809978,"text":"of many different individuals\nand stakeholders"},{"time":813602,"text":"who want to think about how to use\nthis technology responsibly."},{"time":817918,"text":"It may not be possible to come up with\na consensus point of view,"},{"time":821044,"text":"but I think we should at least understand"},{"time":823061,"text":"what all the issues are as we go forward."}]},{"cues":[{"time":825057,"text":"BG: Now, colleagues of yours,"},{"time":826487,"text":"like George Church,\nfor example, at Harvard,"},{"time":828590,"text":"they say, \"Yeah, ethical issues basically\nare just a question of safety."},{"time":832050,"text":"We test and test and test again,\nin animals and in labs,"},{"time":834728,"text":"and then once we feel it's safe enough,\nwe move on to humans.\""},{"time":838668,"text":"So that's kind of the other\nschool of thought,"},{"time":841273,"text":"that we should actually use\nthis opportunity and really go for it."},{"time":844445,"text":"Is there a possible split happening\nin the science community about this?"},{"time":848247,"text":"I mean, are we going to see\nsome people holding back"},{"time":850731,"text":"because they have ethical concerns,"},{"time":852549,"text":"and some others just going forward"},{"time":854260,"text":"because some countries under-regulate\nor don't regulate at all?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":857580,"text":"JD: Well, I think with any new technology,\nespecially something like this,"},{"time":861449,"text":"there are going to be\na variety of viewpoints,"},{"time":864258,"text":"and I think that's\nperfectly understandable."},{"time":867623,"text":"I think that in the end,"},{"time":869159,"text":"this technology will be used\nfor human genome engineering,"},{"time":874134,"text":"but I think to do that without careful\nconsideration and discussion"},{"time":878475,"text":"of the risks and potential complications"},{"time":881436,"text":"would not be responsible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":882999,"text":"BG: There are a lot of technologies\nand other fields of science"},{"time":886002,"text":"that are developing exponentially,\npretty much like yours."},{"time":888797,"text":"I'm thinking about artificial\nintelligence, autonomous robots and so on."},{"time":893199,"text":"No one seems --"},{"time":894390,"text":"aside from autonomous warfare robots --"},{"time":896922,"text":"nobody seems to have launched\na similar discussion in those fields,"},{"time":901651,"text":"in calling for a moratorium."},{"time":903085,"text":"Do you think that your discussion may\nserve as a blueprint for other fields?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":907180,"text":"JD: Well, I think it's hard for scientists\nto get out of the laboratory."},{"time":910723,"text":"Speaking for myself,"},{"time":911900,"text":"it's a little bit\nuncomfortable to do that."},{"time":914540,"text":"But I do think that being involved\nin the genesis of this"},{"time":918478,"text":"really puts me and my colleagues\nin a position of responsibility."},{"time":922358,"text":"And I would say that I certainly hope\nthat other technologies"},{"time":925812,"text":"will be considered in the same way,"},{"time":928482,"text":"just as we would want to consider\nsomething that could have implications"},{"time":931904,"text":"in other fields besides biology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":933855,"text":"BG: Jennifer, thanks for coming to TED."}]},{"cues":[{"time":935831,"text":"JD: Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":937116,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}